In article <3ce63f$lr2@urvile.MSUS.EDU> skriefal@eeyore.stcloud.msus.edu (Scott Kriefall) writes:
>I recently purchased a Sony CDU33A cdrom drive, but have yet to be able
>to get it to work with Warp.  I ran selective install and chose support for
>the CDU31A/CDU33A.  After rebooting, I am still unable to access the
>drive.  Is there a need to modify the cdrom lines in config.sys in some
>way?  Anyone have one of these drives working under Warp?

Nevermind...  I found the problem.  The interface card was set to IRQ 9,
which didn't work.  I moved the jumper to the pins for "no irq", which is 
supposed to be the default, and it works now.
